        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 9:18PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 917 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Hyattville, which is 16 miles east of Basin,
moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph and pea sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...Hyattville and Medicine
Lodge State Archaeological Site around 925 to 930 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Persons in campgrounds, such as Medicine Lodge State Archaeological
Site, should consider seeking sturdy shelter until this storm passes.</instruction>
